A Uruguayan man who was rescued after spending four months apparently lost in the Andes was on the run from child sex allegations, it has emerged.

Raul Fernando Gomez Circunegui, 58, was rescued on Sunday after a group of Argentinians who were recording snow levels stumbled across him.

He lost more than three stone during his apparent ordeal and was extremely malnourished.

But it has since emerged that a warrant was issued for his arrest by authorities in Chile in connection with sex offences back in April.

