Chilean authorities have reportedly requested his extradition in connection with allegations of abuse involving an eight year old boy in Santiago.

The Chilean prosecutor's office said in a statement: 'It is believed that he left Chile through an unauthorised crossing since border police were informed of his ban from leaving the country.'

It was not immediately clear why the 58-year-old plumber and motorcycle enthusiast with no apparent mountaineering experience was so determined to walk across the Chilean frontier.

But he claimed to have traveled to Argentina and then Chile to meet up with fellow motorcyclists.

Gomez had reportedly set out to cross the mountains in May but had to take the journey on by foot because
his motorcycle broke down.

He then claimed to have lost his way during a snowstorm.

